{"type":"message","id":"647faea6","parentId":"b3fd2c2f","timestamp":"2026-02-18T17:43:45.394Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-02-18 19:43 GMT+2] OPERATION: MANUAL RECOVERY & SLEEP.\n\n1.  **Error Report (Manual Fallback):**\n    *   Since `broadcast_log.py` struggles with files/tokens, I will read `logs/performance_audit.log` (tail 10 lines) myself.\n    *   *Output:* Print the raw error lines in the final message.\n\n2.  **Roadmap Creation (`docs/ROADMAP_V6.md`):**\n    *   Write the file with the 3 Phases:\n        *   **Phase 1 (Windows Native):** Kill `ls`/`grep`. Use `pathlib`.\n        *   **Phase 2 (Iron Core):** Compile Rust `.pyd` for Windows.\n        *   **Phase 3 (Cloud Mind):** Docker Deploy.\n\n3.  **Final Output:**\n    *   Create Roadmap file.\n    *   Summary of errors.\n    *   Sleep message."}],"timestamp":1771436625392}}
{"type":"message","id":"29982639","parentId":"647faea6","timestamp":"2026-02-18T17:44:20.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Executing the Recovery Plan**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the action items. First, I need to extract those last ten lines from the performance audit log. Once I have the error report, the roadmap creation will be next. I'll need to define the phases and content for the roadmap document. Finally, I will bundle it all up for presentation.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771436660091_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"logs/performance_audit.log"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771436660221_3","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/ROADMAP_V6.md","content":"# ROADMAP V6: Windows Native & Rust Integration\n\n## Phase 1: Windows Native (Immediate)\n**Goal:** Eliminate POSIX dependency friction and stabilize the file system layer.\n\n- [ ] **Kill `ls`/`grep` subprocess calls:**\n    - Replace shell-outs with Python's native `pathlib` and `shutil`.\n    - Audit all `exec` calls for non-portable commands.\n- [ ] **Path Sanitization:**\n    - Ensure strict usage of `os.path.join` or `Path` objects.\n    - Fix backslash/forward slash impedance mismatches in log parsers.\n- [ ] **Encoding Safety:**\n    - Enforce `encoding='utf-8'` on all file I/O to prevent Windows CP1252 crash loops.\n\n## Phase 2: Iron Core (Performance)\n**Goal:** High-performance log processing and background tasks.\n\n- [ ] **Rust Integration:**\n    - Compile Rust `.pyd` modules specifically for Windows (x64).\n    - Offload heavy log parsing (regex matching) to Rust.\n- [ ] **Structured Concurrency:**\n    - Move away from fire-and-forget threads for critical file operations.\n\n## Phase 3: Cloud Mind (Scalability)\n**Goal:** Environment isolation and portability.\n\n- [ ] **Docker Deployment:**\n    - Containerize the agent for consistent execution regardless of host OS.\n    - Define clear volume mounts for workspace persistence.\n"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4529,"output":451,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4980,"cost":{"input":0.009058,"output":0.005412,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01447}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771436625394}}
